Creating a parking finder app in Flutter involves several steps, including location services, map integration, and UI/UX design. Below is a high-level overview of how to build such an app, along with a sample Flutter code structure.

---

### **Key Features of the Parking Finder App**
1. **Location-based search** – Find parking spots near the user's current location.
2. **Map integration** – Use Google Maps API to display the map and parking spots.
3. **Real-time updates** – Display the availability of parking spots.
4. **User interface** – A clean, intuitive UI to view parking options, filter by price, time, etc.
5. **Notifications** – Alert users when a parking spot becomes available.

---

### **Flutter Code Structure**

#### 1. **Dependencies**
You need to add the following dependencies in `pubspec.yaml`:

```yaml
dependencies:
  flutter:
    sdk: flutter
  google_maps_flutter: ^2.0.7
  location: ^2.0.0
  http: ^0.13.4
```

---

#### 2. **Main App Structure**

```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import 'package:location/location.dart';
import 'package:google_maps_flutter/google_maps_flutter.dart';
import 'package:http/http.dart' as http;

void main() {
  runApp(ParkingFinderApp());
}

class ParkingFinderApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      title: 'Parking Finder',
      theme: ThemeData(
        primarySwatch: Colors.blue,
      ),
      home: ParkingFinderPage(),
    );
  }
}
```

---

#### 3. **Location Services**

```dart
class LocationService {
  final Location _location = Location();

  Future<LocationData> getCurrentLocation() async {
    bool serviceEnabled = await _location.isServiceEnabled(LocationServices.FusedLocationService);
    if (!serviceEnabled) {
      // Handle the case where location services are disabled
      return Future.error("Location services are disabled.");
    }

    final LocationResult locationResult = await _location.getLocation();
    return locationResult;
  }
}
```

---

#### 4. **Map View with Parking Spots**

```dart
class ParkingFinderPage extends StatefulWidget {
  @override
  _ParkingFinderPageState createState() => _ParkingFinderPageState();
}

class _ParkingFinderPageState extends State<ParkingFinderPage> {
  final LocationService _locationService = LocationService();
  GoogleMapController _mapController;
  List<ParkingSpot> _parkingSpots = [];

  @override
  void initState() {
    super.initState();
    _fetchParkingSpots();
  }

  Future<void> _fetchParkingSpots() async {
    final LocationData location = await _locationService.getCurrentLocation();
    final String locationLatitude = location.latitude.toString();
    final String locationLongitude = location.longitude.toString();

    // Fetch parking spots from an API (mocked for this example)
    final response = await http.get(
      'https://api.example.com/parking-spots?lat=$locationLatitude&lon=$locationLongitude',
      headers: {
        'Accept': 'application/json',
      },
    );

    if (response.statusCode == 200) {
      final List<ParkingSpot> spots = [];
      final List<dynamic> data = json.decode(response.body);
      for (var item in data) {
        spots.add(ParkingSpot(
          id: item['id'],
          name: item['name'],
          price: item['price'],
          time: item['time'],
          lat: item['lat'],
          lon: item['lon'],
        ));
      }
      setState(() {
        _parkingSpots = spots;
      });
    }
  }

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text('Parking Finder'),
      ),
      body: Column(
        children: [
          GoogleMap(
            onMapCreated: (controller) {
              setState(() {
                _mapController = controller;
              });
            },
            initialCameraPosition: CameraPosition(
              target: LatLng(37.7749, -122.4194), // San Francisco
              zoom: 14.0,
            ),
            myLocationEnabled: true,
          ),
          Expanded(
            child: ListView.builder(
              itemCount: _parkingSpots.length,
              itemBuilder: (context, index) {
                final spot = _parkingSpots[index];
                return ListTile(
                  title: Text(spot.name),
                  subtitle: Text('Price: \$${spot.price}, Time: ${spot.time}'),
                  trailing: Icon(Icons.info),
                  onTap: () {
                    // Show details or open a new page
                  },
                );
              },
            ),
          ),
        ],
      ),
    );
  }
}
```

